eamTask.initializeTopology() is called during task startup (line 1080)\n   - Iterates through topology.processors() and calls node.init(processorContext, processingExceptionHandler) on each ProcessorNode\n   - This initializes all processor nodes with the execution context\n\n8. **State Management** (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/processor/internals/ProcessorStateManager.java and AbstractTask.java):\n   - ProcessorStateManager manages lifecycle and restoration of state stores\n   - AbstractTask holds the ProcessorTopology and ProcessorStateManager references\n   - State stores are restored from changelog topics and checkpoint files before processors are initialized\n   - Processor context provides access to state stores during processing\n\n**Key Components:**\n- ProcessorNode (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/processor/internals/ProcessorNode.java): Base class for all processor nodes with init() method\n- SourceNode (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/processor/internals/SourceNode.java): Reads from Kafka topics\n- SinkNode (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/processor/internals/SinkNode.java): Writes to Kafka topics\n- Topology (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/Topology.java): User-facing topology representation that wraps InternalTopologyBuilder"
