  "text": "The Kafka Streams topology build and compilation process follows this chain:\n\n1. **User API Entry Point** (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/StreamsBuilder.java):\n   - StreamsBuilder.build() and build(Properties) are the public API methods that users call to compile a topology\n   - They call internalStreamsBuilder.buildAndOptimizeTopology(props) and return the Topology object\n\n2. **High-Level Topology Construction** (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/internals/InternalStreamsBuilder.java):\n   - InternalStreamsBuilder.buildAndOptimizeTopology() orchestrates the compilation process\n   - It merges duplicate source nodes, optimizes topology based on configuration, and enables versioned semantics\n   - Uses a priority queue to traverse GraphNode instances and calls writeToTopology(internalTopologyBuilder) on each node\n   - Each high-level operation (stream, table, etc.) creates a GraphNode that is added to the graph during builder operations\n\n3. **Low-Level Topology Builder** (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/processor/internals/InternalTopologyBuilder.java):\n   - InternalTopologyBuilder is the core class that accumulates all topology information\n   - Maintains three key maps:\n     * nodeFactories (LinkedHashMap): stores NodeFactory instances in topological order for ProcessorNode, SourceNode, and SinkNode creation\n     * stateFactories (HashMap): stores StoreFactory instances for state store management\n     * globalStateBuilders (LinkedHashMap): stores global state store factories\n   - addStateStore() registers StoreFactory instances (wrapped from StoreBuilder) in stateFactories map\n   - buildTopology() and buildSubtopology() methods compile the accumulated topology into ProcessorTopology instances\n   - Inner classes define NodeFactory (abstract), ProcessorNodeFactory, SourceNodeFactory, and SinkNodeFactory\n\n4. **Processor Topology Compilation** (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/processor/internals/InternalTopologyBuilder.java build() method, lines 1012-1060):\n   - The private build(Set<String> nodeGroup) method:\n   - Iterates through all NodeFactory instances in topological order\n   - Calls factory.build() to create ProcessorNode, SourceNode, or SinkNode instances\n   - Calls buildProcessorNode(), buildSourceNode(), or buildSinkNode() to connect nodes and register state stores\n   - Returns a new ProcessorTopology instance containing the compiled processor nodes, topic mappings, and state stores\n\n5. **Compiled Topology Representation** (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/processor/internals/ProcessorTopology.java):\n   - ProcessorTopology is an immutable compiled representation containing:\n   - processorNodes: List<ProcessorNode<?, ?, ?, ?>> - all processor nodes in topological order\n   - sourceNodesByTopic: Map<String, SourceNode<?, ?>> - source nodes indexed by topic\n   - sinksByTopic: Map<String, SinkNode<?, ?>> - sink nodes indexed by topic\n   - stateStores: List<StateStore> - local state stores for this topology\n   - globalStateStores: List<StateStore> - global state stores\n   - storeToChangelogTopic: Map<String, String> - mapping of store names to changelog topics\n\n6. **State Store Registration** (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/processor/internals/StoreBuilderWrapper.java and StoreFactory.java):\n   - StoreBuilder instances are wrapped by StoreBuilderWrapper.wrapStoreBuilder() as StoreFactory implementations\n   - StoreFactory is registered via InternalTopologyBuilder.addStateStore(StoreFactory, String...)\n   - State stores are stored in InternalTopologyBuilder.stateFactories map\n   - During build(), state stores are instantiated and added to ProcessorTopology.stateStores\n\n7. **Runtime Task Initialization** (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/processor/internals/StreamTask.java):\n   - StreamTask extends AbstractTask and receives ProcessorTopology in its constructor\n   - StreamTask.initializeTopology() is called during task startup (line 1080)\n   - Iterates through topology.processors() and calls node.init(processorContext, processingExceptionHandler) on each ProcessorNode\n   - This initializes all processor nodes with the execution context\n\n8. **State Management** (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/processor/internals/ProcessorStateManager.java and AbstractTask.java):\n   - ProcessorStateManager manages lifecycle and restoration of state stores\n   - AbstractTask holds the ProcessorTopology and ProcessorStateManager references\n   - State stores are restored from changelog topics and checkpoint files before processors are initialized\n   - Processor context provides access to state stores during processing\n\n**Key Components:**\n- ProcessorNode (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/processor/internals/ProcessorNode.java): Base class for all processor nodes with init() method\n- SourceNode (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/processor/internals/SourceNode.java): Reads from Kafka topics\n- SinkNode (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/processor/internals/SinkNode.java): Writes to Kafka topics\n- Topology (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/Topology.java): User-facing topology representation that wraps InternalTopologyBuilder"
